                    <h1 style="font-family:serif; font-size: 45px;">For Researcher</h1>
                    <br>
                    <p style="font-family:sans-serif; font-style:italic; font-size: 26px;">Every materials research project entails collection of a large number of microstructure images. Only a very small fraction of them make way into the journal publication and rest all snapshots of the same material are lost in the local desktop. However this data collection is expensive and we believe all data is crucial to research.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p style="font-family:sans-serif; font-style:italic; font-size: 26px;">Hence Microgram! The platform enables you as a researcher to upload all microstructures collected for a project by simply dragging and dropping them from your local desktop. You can tag simple metadata about the microstructures and for further information can link your journal paper to the images. Further more you can control the privacy settings of the images and either keep it private, protected or public. Hence Microgram can be a great tool to collaborate on research within a project as well.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

